Key Takeaways
SSM Parameter Store can expose sensitive data if misconfigured
Always use SecureString type for sensitive parameters
Implement least-privilege IAM policies for parameter access
Regularly audit parameter naming conventions
Monitor parameter access patterns for anomalies
Security Best Practices
Use SecureString type for all sensitive data
Implement parameter path-based access controls
Enable CloudTrail logging for parameter access
Rotate secrets regularly using AWS Secrets Manager
Use KMS encryption for SecureString parameters
Avoid descriptive names that reveal system details
